      faq1Answer: "Standard reverse osmosis removes virtually all dissolved solids from your water, including beneficial minerals like calcium and magnesium. Alkaline RO adds an extra remineralization stage after purification that restores these essential minerals and raises the pH to 8.5-9.5. You get the same deep purification with the added benefit of mineral-rich, great-tasting alkaline water.",
      faq2Question: "Does Aquafeel test my water before recommending a system?",
      faq2Answer: "Absolutely. We never recommend a system without understanding your water first. Our certified technician performs a free in-home water test that reveals exactly what contaminants are present, their concentration levels, and your water's current pH. The results guide our recommendation so you get the system that truly matches your water profile.",
      faq3Question: "How often do the filters and membrane need to be replaced?",
      faq3Answer: "Pre-filters and post-filters are typically replaced every 6 to 12 months depending on your water quality and usage. The RO membrane lasts 2 to 3 years, and the alkaline remineralization cartridge is replaced annually. Aquafeel offers maintenance plans so you never have to think about filter schedules -- we handle it for you.",
      faq4Question: "Is alkaline water safe for the whole family?",
      faq4Answer: "Yes. Mildly alkaline water in the 8.5-9.5 pH range is safe for adults, children, and pets. The minerals added back -- calcium, magnesium, and potassium -- are the same ones found naturally in spring water and mineral water brands. If anyone in your household has specific medical concerns, we recommend consulting with your healthcare provider.",
