      faq2A: "In North Carolina, the most common well water issues are iron and manganese (causing staining and metallic taste), hardness from calcium and magnesium, low pH/acidic water (especially in the Piedmont and Mountain regions), hydrogen sulfide (rotten egg smell), coliform bacteria, and elevated nitrate levels in agricultural areas. The specific mix depends on your geology and well depth.",
